In answer to Grosseteste (Oct 2007), Along Came Betty (a Benny Golson composition from the 50s), like other songs on the album Moanin',   is performed by Art Blakey (drums) and his Jazz Messengers:  Lee Morgan (trumpet), Benny Golson (tenor sax), Bobby Timmons (piano), Jymie Merritt (bass).
This is obviously not from Moanin with Blakey and the Messengers.
I'm not entirely clear as to the point of tagging this with art blakey - along came betty...  Any suggestions?
